Microsoft Dynamics Champion 
Do you love .. banking for entrepreneurs? 
Knab was founded in 2012 because we wanted to do things differently. Simpler, smarter and more advantageous for our customers. Because we believe we can help everyone maximize their financial affairs. "Feel at ease when it comes to your finances. Every day." By combining smart technical solutions with a healthy dose of human intelligence, we create financial services that really meet your needs. Add to that some of the sublime personal service from our employees and you end up with something that's truly unique to the world of finance. From banking to insurances, we've got your back!  
All our colleagues have one thing in common: we help customers to maximize their money matters seamlessly and proactively. We're open-minded, positive and committed to our customers. So, you gain control over your financial affairs 
In a nutshell  
You are our champion on the Microsoft Dynamics CRM platform of the bank. Through your hands-on experience with Microsoft solutions, you guide our CRM team (and other teams) in developing solutions (configuration vs custom code) for our service desk and internal consumers. You help provide even better service to our customers. You have close connections with Microsoft, you act like a Microsoft Most Valuable Professional (MVP) and you are intrinsically motivated to stay up to date and have the latest and greatest of the MSD platform. You are enthusiastic to build the MSD practice within the bank, guide the teams and them bring forward. 
You analyze problems and help determine a solution (or path). You find and implement the best solutions (sometimes in consultation with suppliers). Of course, you will be working on optimizing our Continuous Delivery and get room to improve the team as a whole. 
The Team 
Our business language within Knab is English; 
The CRM team is part of IT Functions & Foundations (ITFF) stream and focusses on developing and maintaining our Customer Relationship Management solution based on Microsoft Dynamics, and the surrounding custom developer services based on C# .NET core. Everything is hosted in cloud (Microsoft Saas, Azure and AWS) glued together by the core network infrastructure of the bank.  
The ITFF department contains multiple Agile teams focusing centralized IT and supports Value Streams which focus on the specific customer propositions. As part of the ITFF stream, you report to the IT Chapter Lead. At Knab you will have the autonomy to pursue your own initiatives and responsibilities. 
At Knab we are organized alongside Value Streams, consisting of multiple Scrum teams, operations departments and a support team. There are two Value Streams organized around our Customer Propositions: Daily Use and Financial Freedom. Next to the valuestreams there is also the supporting stream: IT Functions and Foundations. By organizing this way: we achieve more focus and a higher speed of delivery. 
Your Profile 

High quality is an important factor in your daily job; 
You are able to stay focused; 
You are an excellent team player; 
You understand what needs to be done to automate operations. 
Very good communicator and able to work effectively in teams ask questions, give suggestions, and challenge your peers; 
Curious self-starter able to take initiative and build the best IT solutions for Knab 
Excellent people skills  

Skills and knowledge we would love to see There is not a set route to become a great Network Specialist at Knab, but to be successful in this role, this is the profile we have in mind:   

Dutch speaker and you live in the Netherlands;
Solid experience with Microsoft (Dynamics) Platform (at least 5 years of experience) and experience with development of MS Dynamics Plugins and MS Power Automate; 
A good background in C# and .NET Core (a minimum of 3 years of experience), or similar; 
Deployment: AzureDevOps, Terraform, SonarCloud;
Testing: unit tests and acceptance tests are covered with xUnit, SpecFlow;
Experienced in cloud platforms, preferably AWS; using Terraform to create and maintain the infrastructure (IaC);  and experience with CI/CD (AzureDevOps) and Operational Monitoring Solutions (New Relic).

Work with us! 
If you come to work with us, Knab will become a significant part of your life. Therefore, we make sure the ambiance is just as exciting as your job. Check the benefits here! 
We don't collaborate with third parties to fulfill this role, nor are we open to freelance or contractors.
